DDL (Data Definition Language)
  Common DDL:
    CREATE - creating tables and defining columns
    ALTER - altering tables (add/drop columns, and modify data types)
    TRUNCATE - deleting data in a table, but not the table itself
    DROP - used for deleting tables

DML (Data Manipulation Language)
  CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete rows)
  Common DML:
    INSERT - inserting a row/s into a table
    SELECT - reads or selects rows from a table
    UPDATE - edits row/s from a table
    DELETE - removes a row/s from a table
